File image of headphones and a cellphone JOHANNESBURG - The 2010s will likely be known for music that broke boundaries and records. Billboard recently released the list of the Top 100 Best Songs Of 2010s, which included data from December 5, 2009, through September 28, 2019. READ: 2010s hottest decade in history, UN says as emissions rise again The list ranked according to an inverse point system, with weeks at No. 1 on weekly charts earning the greatest value and weeks at lower positions earning the least. Below is a list of the top ten best songs of 2010s: 10. Rolling In The Deep - Adele 9. Despacito - Luis Fonsi, Justin Bieber & Daddy Yankee 8. Somebody that I used to know - Gotye ft Kimbra 7. Old Town Road - Lil Nas X ft Billy Ray Cyrus 6. We Found Love - Rihanna ft Calvin Harris 5. Girls Like You - Maroon 5 4. Closer - The Chainsmokers ft Halsey 3. Shape Of You - Ed Sheeran 2. Party Rock Anthem - LMFAO ft Lauren Bennet & Goonrock 1. Uptown Funk - Mark Ronson ft Bruno Mars